<HEAD>Malnourished And Badly Battered Child Found On Subway; Parents Charged</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A couple who reported their 7-year-old son missing were charged Monday with child abuse after the bruised and malnourished boy was found on a subway car with cigarette burns and black eyes, police said. <PERSON> Rene </PERSON> <PERSON> Samacarit </PERSON>, 28, and <PERSON> Zorida </PERSON> <PERSON> Maldonado </PERSON>, 31, of <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> were charged with second-degree assault and endangering the welfare of a minor, said police spokesman Sgt. <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Donnell </PERSON>. The couple reported the boy missing at 2:30 p.m. Less than half an hour later, <ORGANIZATION> Transit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> found the malnourished and beaten child on a subway in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION>, <PERSON> O'Donnell </PERSON> said. The boy, who had run away from home, was taken to <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vincent </LOCATION><LOCATION> 's </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> with multiple injuries, including cigarette burns, bruises, black eyes, a throat infection and malnutrition, <PERSON> O'Donnell </PERSON> said His parents identified him at the hospital and were charged following an investigation, <PERSON> O'Donnell </PERSON> said. The boy's 3-year-old sister has been turned over to the <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Child </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Welfare </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> O'Donnell </PERSON> said. The children's names were not released.
