 With 14 seconds left in his 18th and final <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Basketball </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> All-Star Game, <PERSON> Kareem </PERSON> <PERSON> Abdul-Jabbar </PERSON> finally hit a sky hook. After missing five sky hooks, he made his sixth to score the West's final field goal in its 143-134 victory over the East on Sunday. `` I would have been disappointed if it had n't dropped,'' said the 41-year-old <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> Laker center, who is retiring at the end of the season, his 20th season. `` I wanted to get a field goal.'' <PERSON> Abdul-Jabbar </PERSON> was able to play in the game because of an injury to teammate <PERSON> Magic </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>.
