<HEAD>James Caan Crashes On Motorcycle, Suffers Broken Ribs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Actor <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Caan </PERSON> suffered broken ribs after he lost control of his motorcycle and it crashed, police said. <PERSON> Caan </PERSON>, 49, was n't wearing a helmet but suffered no serious head injuries in the crash, which occurred shortly before noon Sunday, said police Lt. <PERSON> Barney </PERSON> <PERSON> Melekian </PERSON>. The crash were under investigation, but there were no sign that <PERSON> Caan </PERSON> was intoxicated, <PERSON> Melekian </PERSON> said. Weather conditions were clear and no other vehicles were involved. Besides fractured ribs, the actor suffered minor facial cuts and bruises, said <PERSON> Corinne </PERSON> <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON>, nursing supervisor at <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Johns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, where <PERSON> Caan </PERSON> was listed in good condition. <PERSON> Caan </PERSON> played <PERSON> Sonny </PERSON> <PERSON> Corleone </PERSON>, the hot-headed son of the Mafia chieftain in the Oscar-winning film `` The Godfather,'' and portrayed terminally ill <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> Bears football running back <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Piccolo </PERSON> in the TV movie `` <PERSON> Brian </PERSON>'s Song.'' His other credits include `` Rollerball,'' `` Cinderella Liberty,'' `` A Bridge Too Far,'' `` Freebie and the Bean'' and `` Rabbit Run.'' The crash came two months after actor <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> crashed his Harley-Davidson while riding without a helmet. He suffered serious head injuries but is improving. Like <PERSON> Busey </PERSON>, <PERSON> Caan </PERSON> was riding a <LOCATION> Harley </LOCATION>.
