<HEAD>Poll Reached 1,162 Respondents</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Poll-Israel-PLO, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 This <ORGANIZATION> Media </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General-Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> poll is based on telephone interviews Jan. 4-12 with 1,162 adults in the continental <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The phone numbers were selected randomly and interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent birthday. The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample. The poll has a 3 percentage-point margin of error, meaning that if every adult American were asked the same questions, the results theoretically would be the within 3 points of the poll's results, 19 times out of 20. The error margin is larger for subgroups _ 5 points, for example, among college graduates. Other sources of potential error in polls include the wording and order of questions. These are the questions in this poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100: 1. Do you approve or disapprove of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> holding talks with the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>, known as the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>? Approve: 67 percent. Disapprove: 17 percent. Do n't know or no answer: 16 percent. 2. Should <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> negotiate with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, or not? Yes: 62. No: 15. DK-NA: 24. 3. Should the <LOCATION> Palestinians </LOCATION> have their own country, or not? Yes: 62. No: 11. DK-NA: 27. 4. Do you believe that the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> has given up terrorism, or do you think it's only saying that for political advantage? Believe: 6. Disbelieve: 74. DK-NA: 20. 5. Do you think the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> wants to destroy <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, or do you think it would accept a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state coexisting with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>? Destroy: 33. Coexist: 36. DK-NA: 32. 6. If the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> recognizes <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s right to exist, should <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> give up territory it occupies and allow creation of a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state there? Yes: 44. No: 25. DK-NA: 31. 6a. -LRB- If yes to 6 -RRB- Should Israeli settlers in that territory be required to leave, or not? Yes: 27. No: 62. DK-NA: 11. 7. Do you think that only the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> can represent the Palestinians in negotiations with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, or could some other group do it _ for example, a delegation of Palestinians and Jordanians? PLO: 11. Other: 63. DK-NA: 26. 8. Should the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> try to force <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> to negotiate with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> by threatening sanctions if <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> refuses? Yes: 16. No: 67. DK-NA: 17. 9. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> has declared the creation of an independent Palestinian state, without defining its boundaries. Do you think the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> should recognize that state? Yes: 23. No: 52. DK-NA: 25. 10. Do you think pro-Israel groups in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> have too much influence on <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> policy, or too little, or about the right amount? Much: 35. Little: 8. Right: 32. DK-NA: 25. 11. How about pro-Palestinian groups in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> _ do you think they have too much influence on <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> policy, or too little, or about the right amount? Much: 20. Little: 18. Right: 33. DK-NA: 30.
