<HEAD>Minor Earthquakes Shake Northern California</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to UPDATE with USGS reducing Richter reading
to 3.0 sted 3.6; picks up 4th graf pvs, ``We had ...''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERKELEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A mild earthquake early today shook a wide area of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>, the sixth tremor in <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> within 24 hours, officials said. No damage or injuries were immediately reported from the quakes, whose magnitudes ranged from 2.4 to 3.0 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale. The sixth quake struck at 12:01 a.m. and had a magnitude of 3.0 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale, according to the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> States </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Geological </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Survey </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Earthquake </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Information </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Golden </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colo </LOCATION>. It was centered west of the <LOCATION> Golden </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gate </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bridge </LOCATION>, the same area as two earlier ones, said seisomologist <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Lomax </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Seismology </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Station </ORGANIZATION>. `` We had several calls from all over the city but so far no reports of damage,'' said a <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> police dispatcher who declined to give his name. The first quake, which measured 2.7 on the Richter scale, struck at 11:49 a.m. Sunday and was centered about five miles west of the bridge. Within two minutes, two more quakes, measuring 2.6 and 2.4 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale, were felt in southern <LOCATION> Marin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Lomax </PERSON> said. At 10 p.m., a magnitude 3.0 quake struck the same general area off the Golden Gate as the first one, <PERSON> Lomax </PERSON> said. A quake that measured 2.9 was centered near <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Leandro </LOCATION>, about 10 miles south of <LOCATION> Berkeley </LOCATION>, at 10:41 p.m., he said. The <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on seismographs. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase in magnitude. A quake of magnitude 3.5 can cause slight damage. The <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> earthquake of 1906 measured an estimated 8.3 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale.
