phase in her life and welcome to being a woman.'' <PERSON> Werner </PERSON> said the episode was probably originally the idea of writer <PERSON> McKeaney </PERSON>, though it would have been developed by the writers with <PERSON> Barr </PERSON> and was a subject almost everyone on the show could relate to in some way. `` I'm going through it as a father,'' <PERSON> Werner </PERSON> said. `` Roseanne obviously has gone through it as a mother. <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Harris </PERSON>, who is the head writer, has gone through it as a father. I think we're excited about it because I think it was handled in a well-crafted way, and I think it made its point without being too heavy-handed.''
