<HEAD>Iran To Hang 70 Drug Smugglers in One Day</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By NEIL MacFARQUHAR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> says it will hang 70 drug traffickers Tuesday, the highest number to be executed in one day in that nation's fierce anti-narcotics crackdown aimed at stopping the flow to at least 1 million addicts. Hard-line Prosecuter-General <PERSON> Musavi </PERSON> <PERSON> Khoeiniha </PERSON> said in a recent radio interview: `` This is the end of the line. If we do not destroy them -LRB- drug smugglers -RRB- they will destroy our youths.'' Khoeiniha first gained fame in 1979 as the guiding hand behind the militant extremists who stormed the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION>, holding 52 hostages for 444 days. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> instituted a new law on Jan. 21 that includes the death penalty for anyone found with 30 grams -LRB- just over an ounce -RRB- of heroin or five kilograms -LRB- 11 pounds -RRB- of opium or hashish. Addicting someone else carries a 20-year sentence. The law coincided with a crackdown that put helicopter gunships into the air along the borders with <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Afghanistan </LOCATION> to track smugglers. On Jan. 16, a record 56 drug smugglers were executed. The official <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION>, says 105 smugglers have been executed since Dec. 31. The Iranian resistance group <ORGANIZATION> Mujahedeen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Khalq </ORGANIZATION> accuses the Iranian government of creating hysteria over the drug problem as a means of extending a siege mentality and eliminating its enemies following the 8-year Iran-Iraq war. An <ORGANIZATION> IRNA </ORGANIZATION> report on Tuesday's executions said 10 will be hanged in <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> and the rest in cities throughout <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. Executions were suspended during a 10-day celebration that en