<BYLINE>By LAURINDA KEYS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three black men have signed statements saying <PERSON> Winnie </PERSON> <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON> was `` involved in the events'' the night her bodyguards abducted and beat them, their lawyer said Monday. Mrs. <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON>, a black activist and the wife of jailed <ORGANIZATION> African </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> leader <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON> <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON>, denies the allegations. Her daughter, <PERSON> Zindzi </PERSON>, was quoted Monday as saying Mrs. <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON> will sue the Sunday Star, an anti-apartheid newspaper that reported she helped whip the victims. The men, aged 20 to 29, were released from Mrs. <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON>'s home after community leaders intervened. The three earlier had been identified as being teen-agers. A fourth youth, 14-year-old <PERSON> Moeketsi </PERSON> `` Stompie'' <PERSON> Seipei </PERSON>, is missing and feared dead. Prominent anti-apartheid lawyer <PERSON> Geoff </PERSON> <PERSON> Budlender </PERSON> said his three clients are considering legal action. The three `` say they were abducted _ three of them and <PERSON> Stompie </PERSON> _ and they were all assaulted on the first night. They say she -LRB- Mrs. <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON> -RRB- was involved in the events on the first night,'' said <PERSON> Budlender </PERSON>. `` They say <PERSON> Stompie </PERSON> was removed from them a day or two afterward and they never saw him again.'' He declined to elaborate, saying his clients have not authorized him to release details of the statements they gave him. Mrs. <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON>, 54, has denied she was at home when the bodyguards, known as the <ORGANIZATION> Mandela </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> soccer team, brought the four there late last month. But she also has defended the bodyguards, saying they took the four from a <ORGANIZATION> Methodist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church <