rough tolls, as part of a plan to replace the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> Turnpike with the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Parkway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tourism </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Caperton </PERSON> proposed two constitutional amendments: one to eliminate the jobs of agriculture commissioner, secretary of state and treasurer; and one to allow cities and counties to decide on their own form of government, including the possibility of forming joint municipal-county governments or even merging two or more counties. Gubernatorial aide <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Reale </PERSON> said the proposed amendments, which must be approved by two-thirds of both the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delegates </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>, probably would be placed on the ballot for voter ratification in a special election this fall. The 5 percent pay raise for teachers and state employees would depend on whether the state can save $ 40 million to $ 45 million in the first six months of the 1989-90 fiscal year.
