<HEAD>SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD>
<HEAD>Fashion: Petites</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY706</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 That the small woman wants more than revised versions of her taller sister's clothes is attested by her open checkbook at cash registers. The petite lines, whether dresses, suits or sportswear, has outpaced all other categories of ready-to-wear in sales. Industry figures for a six-year period show a growth rate of almost twice for that for the overall misses and sportswear lines. Despite estimates that nearly 55 percent of all adult <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> women are 5-feet-3 or under, there was a time was the smaller woman was left with a choice of paying for alterations or just rolling up her sleeves. That has changed. Now, nearly all major apparel manufacturers have petite lines, and most large stores have departments or boutiques devoted to the small woman. Typically, petite-size styling differs from regular misses sizes in shorter sleeves, hems and waist lengths. Details are to scale, too. There will be one or two buttons on a suit jacket instead of two or three, and the shoulder pads will be lighter and less bulky. `` Little girl'' touches, such as ruffles, bows and puffy sleeves, are avoided. `` The petite woman is looking for excellent design and quality, and she wants it in the proportion and fit that is right for her,'' said <PERSON> Bernard </PERSON> <PERSON> Olsoff </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> Frederick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Atkins </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a merchandising and marketing firm that has been tracking sales for about 30 department store chains. He said there has been a 143 percent compounded growth rate over six years for petite dresses and 350 percent for petite sportswear. This contrasts with 77 percent and 82 percent in those categories of misses sizes. `` When you're on the small side, you look for tailored, well-made fashions that do n't overwhelm you,'' said <PERSON> Gretchen </PERSON> <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlson </PERSON>, the current <LOCATION> Miss </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>. `` I like clothing that fits well at the waist, such as shorter jackets and belted styles.'' Ms. <PERSON> Carlson </PERSON>, who stands 5-feet-3 -LCB-, is celebrity representative for Crafted with Pride in <ORGANIZATION> U.S.A. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>, a manufacturers trade group.
