<HEAD>EEC Jobless Rate Fell To 10 Percent In December</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The unemployment rate in the 12-nation <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION> fell to a nearly five-year low of 10 percent in December, the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> reported Monday. The trade block's statistical service, <ORGANIZATION> Eurostat </ORGANIZATION>, said 15.6 million people were unemployed in the region at the end of December, up 1.1 percent from 15.43 million in November. The jobless rate in November was 10.1 percent. For all of 1988, the average number of jobless fell 1.25 percent to 15.9 million compared with 16.1 million in 1987. The <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> last had an umeployment rate of 10 percent in summer of 1983. Unemployment peaked at 11 percent in the fall of 1984, <ORGANIZATION> Eurostat </ORGANIZATION> reported.
