surance markets as well as signing a five-year agreement with <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION>. Annual revenue rose to $ 4.84 billion from $ 4.43 billion in 1987. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hughes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electronics </ORGANIZATION> said its fourth-quarter 1988 earnings rose to $ 169.5 million, or 43 cents a share, from $ 145.5 million, or 36 cents a share, during the same quarter in 1987. Revenue during fourth quarter 1988 was $ 3.1 billion, up from $ 2.7 billion a year earlier. For the entire year, <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hughes </ORGANIZATION> earned $ 653.3 million, or $ 2.01 a share, up 25.3 percent from $ 521.1 million, or $ 1.67 per share, in 1987 profits. Annual revenues rose to $ 11.2 billion last year from $ 10.5 billion in 1987. The earnings include the impact of a first quarter accounting change, which boosted net income by $ 18.7 million. EDS earnings are the base for <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Class </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> E </ORGANIZATION> stock and <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hughes </ORGANIZATION> profits are linked to <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION>'s Class H stock. Last week, <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> announced a 20 percent increase in its dividend and a 2-for-1 split of its common stocks. Dividends rose 41 percent for <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION>'s Class E stock and 64 percent for <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> Class H stock. <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s earnings are expected to be announced Thursday. On Feb. 2, <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> posted a fourth quarter profit of $ 433.6 million, or $ 1.85 per share, and annual earnings of $ 1.05 billion, or $ 4.66 a share, down 18.6 percent from 1987. The Big Three automakers are expected to earn a total of about $ 11 billion in 1988, breaking the companies' combined 1984 earnings record of $ 9.79 billion.
