<HEAD>GM Moving Some Truck Production To Wisconisn</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB SCHMALFELDT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it will shift production of three light-duty trucks to a <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> plant from <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> in 1991. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Klipstine </PERSON> also said the automaker would put production of at least one new truck line in its <LOCATION> Flint </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, plant, which has about 3,800 workers to compensate for the switch to a plant in <LOCATION> Janesville </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> said production of its Chevrolet Suburban and Blazer trucks and the <ORGANIZATION> GMC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jimmy </ORGANIZATION> utility vehicles would be moved from <LOCATION> Flint </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Janesville </LOCATION> in 1991 for the 1992 model year. Gov. <PERSON> Tommy </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Thompson </PERSON> announced the move in <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> Janesville </LOCATION> plant, which employs about 5,700 people, currently produces the <ORGANIZATION> Buick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Skylark </ORGANIZATION> and the Chevrolet Cavalier compact models. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> said those lines would be phased out to make room for the new truck lines. <PERSON> Klipstine </PERSON> said decisions on employment, production speeds and the length of retooling time for both plants is unknown. It is likely that both plants will be shut down to refit machines to make the new products. He said he did not know what <LOCATION> Flint </LOCATION>'s new truck would be or when it would be announced. `` Those are the kinds of things we wo n't know until we learn what kind of product line is coming into <LOCATION> Flint </LOCATION>,'' he said. `` We're talking about something that's going to happen in 1991. The Flint plant now produces 32 vehicles an hour and made about 136,000 vehicles in 1988. In April, it will begin production of crew cab and cab chassis light-duty truck models now being made in <LOCATION> Janesville </LOCATION>.
