<HEAD>New Coal Fields Worth $2.56 Billion Found In Malaysia, Says Report</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A West German team has found two coal deposits containing about 93 million tons of coal worth an estimated $ 2.56 billion, it was reported Tuesday. The two deposits were found in the Tebulan and Merit South areas of <LOCATION> Sarawak </LOCATION> state, <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Straits </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> reported, quoting S.P. <PERSON> Chen </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Sarawak </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Geological </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Survey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> director. The coal is of the sub-bituminous type suitable for industrial use as fuel. The new areas are adjacent to the existing <LOCATION> Merit </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pila </LOCATION> coal field, 180 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Kuching </LOCATION>, which was discovered last April and has about 63.7 million tons of coal worth more than $ 1.72 billion, <PERSON> Chen </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Chen </PERSON> said the discovery was part of a $ 1.1 million-dollar survey being conducted by seven West German geologists since 1983. The seven are in <LOCATION> Sarawak </LOCATION> as part of a German technical aid program that ends in 1990. <PERSON> Chen </PERSON> said there were about 78 million tons of coal in the <LOCATION> Tebulan </LOCATION> area and 15 million tons in Merit South. Commercial mining at the <LOCATION> Merit </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pila </LOCATION> coal field began last June by the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> States-based </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Global </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mineral </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exploration </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and a Malaysian-South Korean joint venture, <ORGANIZATION> Lucky </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Chen </PERSON> said. Global was expected to produce 350,000 tons annually and Lucky Hill 120,000 tons. So far, Global has produced 29,500 tons and Lucky Hill 20,500 tons. The coal is being exported to <LOCATION> Taiwan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>.
